Saved!
Job Details
Cooks perform some or all of the following duties:Prepare and cook complete meals or individual dishes and foodsPrepare and cook special meals for patients as instructed by dietitian or chefSchedule and supervise kitchen helpersOversee kitchen operationsMaintain inventory and records of food, supplies and equipmentMay set up and oversee buffetsMay clean kitchen and work areaMay plan menus, determine size of food portions, estimate food requirements and costs, and monitor and order suppliesMay hire and train kitchen staff.
Requirements
Completion of secondary school is usually required.Completion of a three-year apprenticeship program for cooks orCompletion of college or other program in cooking orSeveral years of commercial cooking experience are required
